   <text>
      <front>
         <p>1889 May 16: to Harding<note xml:id="ftn3-446" place="foot" n="446"> ATL MS-Copy-Micro-0485-1.</note>
         </p>
      </front>
      <body>
         <p rend="end">Thursday night<lb/>May 16 1889</p>
         <p>Mr RC Harding</p>
         <p>My Dear Sir</p>
         <p>Thanks for the ½ doz. copies: I have posted for England, tho’ <hi rend="italic">not</hi> at 3d. each.——</p>
         <p>I leave (D.V.) by 3 p.m. train tomorrow—<hi rend="italic">cannot </hi>endure the <hi rend="italic">early</hi> mg’s. <hi rend="italic">cold</hi>.—–</p>
         <p>I am thinking a little would not be unacceptable &amp; so I enclose a chq. for <hi rend="italic">₤10</hi> on acct., remainder on my return.</p>
         <p>It has occurred to me, to write to the Govr. (Premier) <hi rend="italic">re </hi>my Ty. of W. Ms.—and I think I shall do so: I seek <hi rend="italic">little</hi> for myself: &amp; Dy. can get it out in style—<hi rend="italic">as to binding</hi>, &amp;c.—</p>
         <p>Shall be glad to get a line from you, <hi rend="italic">addd. Dannevirke.</hi>
         </p>
         <p>“Typo”—I take w. me.—I noticed <hi rend="underline italic">your</hi>
            <hi rend="italic"> origin</hi> of “Te Kooti”—<hi rend="italic">I greatly doubt it! </hi>Whence?—–</p>
         <p>Sorry to hear from yr. brother no better account of your Father.—–</p>
         <p>Excuse haste, &amp;c.—</p>
         <p>Yours sincerely</p>
         <p>W. Colenso.</p>
      </body>
